title: Who is Jasmine Yarbrough? | Daily Mail Online
text: Share She set up the brand in 2013 with Tamie Ingham. The Brisbane-born designer is also a model with Chic Management and has appeared in campaigns such as Midori. Past boyfriends: The 5'10 beauty has been previously linked to Australian Wallabies player and Delta Goodrem's ex Drew Mitchell (pictured above) who she dated on and off for years The 5'10 beauty is currently based in LA and has been previously linked to Australian Wallabies player and Delta Goodrem's ex Drew Mitchell who she dated on and off for years. Last year, the former brunette was seen partying at infamous annual week-long party festival based in Nevada. According to Woman's Day , Karl and Jasmine are 'so committed to each other' that they are 'looking for a place to rent together in Sydney.' Model looks: The Brisbane-born designer is also a model with Chic Management and has appeared in campaigns such as Midori Spotted: Just days after it was first reported Karl Stefanovic (left) is dating shoe designer Jasmine Yarbrough (right), the pair have been spotted together for the first time while on a boat party on Sydney Harbour on Saturday and are looking to 'move in together' Ready to meet the family? The 33-year-old blonde beauty is said to have been invited by the TV star to his brother Peter Stefanovic's April wedding to co-star Sylvia Jeffreys, giving her a chance to meet the family And things are getting serious enough that the pair have 'pressed fast forward' on plans to introduce the blonde beauty to family and friends. A source told the publication: 'Jasmine plans to meet Karl's family and get closer to them over the next month while she's in Australia.' 'Families from both side have been very supporting and accepting of their relationship,' the source added. It's believed the couple, who are said to have met on a boat party in December and have been seeing each other since Christmas. 'Smitten': According to The Sunday Telegraph, a friend claims the TV presenter is 'smitten' with the beauty and sees her 'as a legitimate long-term love prospect' Fun on the sea: It's reported the pair met on a boat party in Sydney in December (Karl pictured at a separate boat party with friends in January 2015) The Today host is set to introduce his children, Jackson, 17, Ava, 11 and 10-year-old River to Jasmine. 'Jasmine is a generous, fun-loving, down-to-earth Aussie girl. Karl knows his kids will love her if they're able to give her a chance,' the source added. And according to the Sunday Telegraph, a friend claims the TV presenter is 'smitten' with the beauty and sees her 'as a legitimate long-term love prospect'. The usually LA based Jasmine was spotted in Sydney earlier last week, just after news broke of the coupling. The father-of-three split from his wife of 21-years, Cassandra Thorburn, last year. Happy holidays! It's believed the pair have been seeing each other since before Christmas Split: The father-of-three split from his wife of 21-years, Cassandra Thorburn, last year According to the earlier reports in the weekly tabloid magazine, the duo were preparing to 'go public' soon, according to one of Karl's friends. They claimed: 'Karl and Jasmine don't want to hide because they aren't ashamed of being together'. The 33-year-old blonde beauty is said to have been invited by the TV star to his brother Peter Stefanovic's April wedding to co-star Sylvia Jeffreys, giving her a chance to meet the family. 'They aren't ashamed of being together': According to the earlier reports in the weekly tabloid magazine, the duo were preparing to 'go public' soon, according to one of Karl's friends 'They're hoping that once they declare they're a couple, public interest will die down,' the friend claims. The designer counts Australian models Ashley Hart and Montana Cox among her friends over in the States. It's understood Karl visited the LA-based shoe designer while in the US on his two-month holiday across December and January. The magazine claims the pair travelled separately to restaurants. Representatives from the Nine Network declined Daily Mail Australia's request for comment. Jasmine has also been contacted for comment. Catch-up: It's understood Karl visited the LA-based shoe designer (centre) while in the US on his two-month holiday across December and January Karl recently told the Herald Sun of his marriage to Cassandra, 'I hope I can try and rebuild whatever has happened in the past and try and make the most of what I can do with them in the future.' 'Life is life. People make mistakes. People have break ups. People mostly try to do their best and sometimes they fail,' he added. 'I think that we will work through it as best we can.'
